body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Zoom Auto Care. My name is Jose Kelly. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, Jose. My name is Olivia Stewart.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Olivia. Can you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, two three four, eight nine zero one

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Olivia. Now, could you also share with me your email address?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Olivia. Is there anything specific you need assistance with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I had a question regarding returns, but it has been resolved. I am feeling relieved now.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that, Olivia. If you have any other questions in the future, feel free to reach out. Thank you for your time.
